                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person91" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the watch-house-keeper's wife. I remember the girl, 
               <persName id="t18180114-5-person92">
                  Mary 
                  Alder
               <interp inst="t18180114-5-person92" type="surname" value="Alder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person92" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person92" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , being brought into the watch-house - I searched her, and found two seals on her, one of which Keats, the prosecutor, claimed. The other Mr. Keats said was not his property. She had them in her pockets.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180114-5-person93">
                  ELIZA 
                  DOBSON
               <interp inst="t18180114-5-person93" type="surname" value="DOBSON"></interp>
