            . I am an officer of Marlborough-street Office; I took the prisoners into custody. I did not find any thing on either of them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180114-5-person111">
                  MARY 
                  ALDER
               <interp inst="t18180114-5-person111" type="surname" value="ALDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person111" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person111" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            'S Defence. I have nothing further to say, than that my brother is perfectly innocent of breaking the desk.</p>
               <p>JAMES ALDER'S Defence. I never had any thing to do with the robbery, and know nothing about it. The prosecutor bought all the property knowing it to be stolen. I saw every bit of it bought myself. The officer that has been called and another, have come into the house to search for stolen goods, when the prosecutor has kept them in the parlour, while this girl, my sister, has thrown stolen pots down the privy.</p>
               <p>Prisoner 
               <persName id="t18180114-5-person112">
                  SARAH 
                  WILSON
               <interp inst="t18180114-5-person112" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
