             re-examined. I am sure that the prisoner, 
               <persName id="t18180114-5-person114">
                  James 
                  Alder
               <interp inst="t18180114-5-person114" type="surname" value="Alder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person114" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-5-person114" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , came into the room with the other two prisoners, and I am positive he took the chisel out of his pocket, and broke the desk open; I saw him again in the evening, when he gave me a shilling. I was sitting near the fire-it is not a very large room, and the table was near the fire. I was near enough to the table to see the marks on the spoons.</p>
